oc:kn_17d780c0 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing any file within a plugin command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for all plugin-internal paths — scripts, templates, configuration, and resources — instead of relative paths like ./ which resolve to the current working directory, not the plugin root." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Relative paths break when the command is invoked from different working directories; CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT ensures portable, installation-agnostic file references." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_1814bfc2 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing plugin command scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep commands focused on one clear purpose. Delegate complex logic to scripts, use agents for multi-step workflows, and reference skills for specialized domain knowledge." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Focused commands are easier to test, maintain, and compose into larger workflows." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_24b38ce0 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When naming plugin commands" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid generic command names like /test, /run, or /do-stuff that conflict with common names or lack descriptiveness. Use hyphenated multi-word names and consider prefixing with the plugin name for uniqueness." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Generic names cause conflicts with other plugins or built-in commands and make discovery harder in /help listings." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_3217086c a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building plugin commands end-to-end" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Place .md files in plugin-name/commands/ for auto-discovery. 2. Use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for all internal path references. 3. Validate inputs early with bash checks or inline conditionals. 4. Integrate with plugin agents (Task tool), skills (name reference), and hooks (automatic event triggers). 5. Provide graceful error handling with helpful messages and alternatives." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_36a92d0b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any plugin command that accepts arguments or depends on files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Plugin commands should validate inputs early — check required arguments, verify file existence, and validate argument formats before processing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Early validation prevents cryptic errors downstream and provides actionable error messages to users." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_92d3748f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When troubleshooting plugin command variable expansion failures" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT is not expanding, verify: (1) the command is loaded from a plugin, (2) bash execution is allowed in allowed-tools, and (3) the syntax is exactly ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} with curly braces." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the three most common causes of variable expansion failure in plugin commands." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_b43848c1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When organizing plugin commands into directories" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use subdirectory namespaces when a plugin has 5+ commands to logically group related commands. Subdirectory names become namespaces shown as (plugin:plugin-name:namespace) in /help." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Namespacing improves discoverability and reduces cognitive load for users browsing available commands." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_ca22df61 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing plugin scripts and templates in command frontmatter" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """Run analysis: !`node ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/scripts/analyze.js $1`
Read template: @${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/templates/report.md""" .

oc:kn_e7da8543 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When authoring a new plugin command" ;
    oc:directiveContent """---
description: [action description]
allowed-tools: [tools]
argument-hint: [arg-format]
---

[Command body with ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} references, $1/$2 arguments, and validation]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT",
        "action description",
        "arg-format",
        "tools" .

oc:kn_fca3d8f3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a new plugin command" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Plugin commands are auto-discovered from the commands/ directory at plugin load time — no manual registration required. Commands appear in /help with the (plugin:plugin-name) label." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Understanding the auto-discovery mechanism is essential to placing command files correctly." .

